signals.name: dateRangeStart
signals.comment: Along with dateRangeEnd, these are hard limits on the dates shown. May need to update when we hit 2021. Dates are in milliseconds, unix epoch

signals.name: dateBin
signals.comment: Binning of observations by date, where date is in milliseconds. Default is 1 day (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 = 86400000). This should never be less than a day. This is passed to the bin transform of cases_by_date_and_group. (1 week = 604800000)

signals.name: yearStart
signals.comment: January 1st, 1950 in milliseconds, unix epoch time. Used to demarcate years

signals.name: yearBin
signals.comment: milliseconds per year, used to color the background when multiple years are displayed

signals.name: clear
signals.comment: If clicking on anything but a grouped bar, then clear the selection (by clearing the 'selection' data object)

signals.name: shift
signals.comment: Track whether or not the shift key is pressed. Used to select multiple groups by holding down shift before clicking

signals.name: clicked
signals.comment: Track clicks on the group bars, for selection purposes

transform.comment: Bin observations by date. The width of each bin is determined by the signal dateBin. Since the most detail in the date from GISAID is by day, the bin shouldn't ever be smaller than a day.
Recalculate the day_end from the day_start and dateBin, since the imputation can't work on more than one field at once.

data.name: selected
data.comment: A list of groups that are selected

tooltip.signal: {title: datum.location, 'Sequences': format(datum[yField], tooltipCountFormat), 'Total Location Counts': datum.location_counts, 'Collection date': timeFormat(datum.day_start, '%b %d %Y')}
